      "body" : ">(If someone wanted to immediately re-lock, it seems easier to do it synchronously with the walletlock RPC, than to wait for the async callback and poll the locked-state in a loop)\r\n\r\nI wonder if there's an argument around a JSON-RPC batch that unlocks, runs some method, and re-locks... Probably wouldn't work today, but might be worth adding?",
